{"parse":{"title":"bulb","pageid":39588,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n[[Image:Snowdrop Galanthus gracilis.jpg|thumb|right|Flowers growing from a bulb (lower left)]]\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|id=plant portion|:der|la:bulbus<id:bulb>|tree=1}}\n{{inh+|en|enm|bulb}}, {{m|enm|bolbe}}, from {{der|en|la|bulbus|t=bulb, onion}}, from {{der|en|grc|βολβός|t=plant with round swelling on underground stem}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|bŭlb}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈbʌlb/}}\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈbʌb/|a=Southern US,AAVE,obsolete|ref={{R:Hall PGSMS|3|2|88}}}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-bulb.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌlb|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q188748}}The bulb-shaped underground portion of a plant such as a tulip, consisting of a shortened stem and many fleshy scale leaves, from which the rest of the plant may be regrown.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2005|author=w:Plato|title=Sophist|translator=Lesley Brown|page=265c\n|passage=the plants which grow in the earth from seed or '''bulbs'''.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Val Bourne|title=The quiet man of the world of snowdrops|work={{w|The Daily Telegraph}} (London)|date=7 February 2015|page=G8|passage=Once it [a [[snowdrop]] variety] became established, some '''bulbs''' were lifted and passed on to be chipped (i.e. cut into small pieces and grown on).}}\n# {{lb|en|dated|neuroanatomy}} The {{l|en|medulla oblongata}}.\n# Any solid object rounded at one end and tapering on the other, possibly attached to a larger object at the tapered end.\n#: {{co|en|the '''bulb''' of the aorta}}\n## A [[light bulb]] (not necessarily bulbous in shape).\n##: {{co|en|an incandescent '''bulb'''}}\n##: {{co|en|an LED '''bulb'''}}\n##: {{co|en|a fluorescent tube '''bulb'''}}\n# {{lb|en|nautical}} A bulbous [[protuberance]] at the forefoot of certain vessels to reduce [[turbulence]].\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} An [[onion]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|bulbar|bulbectomy|wet bulb| bulb horn|bulbitis|bulbless|bulblet|bulblike|bulboid|bulbophile|bulby|endbulb|gliobulb|hemibulb|Mandelbulb|pseudobulb|rebulb|wet bulbing|lamp bulb|bulb tee|bulb-out|not the brightest bulb|light bulb|flashbulb|tulip bulb|bus bulb|dim bulb|dim-bulb|dry bulb temperature|dry-bulb temperature|Edison bulb|hair bulb|hot bulb|lamp-bulb|not the brightest bulb in the chandelier|urethral bulb|wet bulb temperature|wet-and-dry-bulb hygrometer|wet-bulb|wet-bulb temperature|bulbhead|bulbheaded}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col3|en\n|bulbiferous\n|bulbil\n|bulbous}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|bulb-shaped underground portion of a plant}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|սոխուկ}}, {{t+|hy|կոճղեզ}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|лу́ковица|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|bulb|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|鱗莖|tr=línjīng}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|bulva|f}}, {{t+|cs|hlíza|f}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|løg|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|bloembol|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{t+|eo|bulbo}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|sibul}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|sipuli}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|bulbe|m}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|bulbo|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|ბოლქვი}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Zwiebel|f}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|βολβός|m}}\n*: Ancient Greek: {{t|grc|βολβός|m}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t-needed|haw}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|בָּצָל|m|tr=batzál}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|virághagyma}}, {{t+|hu|gumó}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|laukur|m}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|bulbo}}\n* Indonesian: {{t+|id|umbi lapis}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|pumppu}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|bleib|f}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|bulbo|m}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|球根|tr=きゅうこん, kyūkon}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|មើម}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|알뿌리}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|bulbus|m}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|луковица|f}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|bebawang}}\n* Malayalam: {{t+|ml|കിഴങ്ങ്}}\n* Māori: {{t-check|mi|tōpuku}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t+|nb|løk|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|løk|m}}\n* Occitan: {{t|oc|bulb|m}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|پیاز|tr=piyâz}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|cebulka|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|bulbo|m}}\n* Rarotongan: {{t|rar|kiko}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|bulb|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|лу́ковица|f}}\n* Samoan: {{t-needed|sm}}\n* Sanskrit: {{t+|sa|कन्द|m}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|bolgan|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|луковица|f}}, {{t|sh|чебуљица|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|lukovica|f}}, {{t|sh|čebuljica|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|cibuľka|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|čebulica|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|bulbo|m}}, {{t+|es|cabeza|f}} {{qualifier|garlic}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|lök|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{t-needed|tl}}\n* Tahitian: {{t-needed|ty}}\n* Tongan: {{t-needed|to}}\n* Turkish:\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|صوغان|tr=soğan}}, {{t|ota|بصل|tr=basal}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t+|uk|цибу́лина|f}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|rounded solid object}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|泡|tr=pāo}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|bol}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|kupu}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|bulbe|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|βολβός|m}}\n* Ido: {{t+|io|bulbo}}\n* Luhya: {{t|luy|eglopu}}\n* Malayalam: {{t|ml|ബൾബ്}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|bulbo|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|bulb|m}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|утолще́ние|n}}, {{t+|ru|вы́пуклость|f}}, {{t+|ru|ша́рик|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|bulbo|m}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|glopu}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|light bulb}}\n\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Telugu: {{t-check|te|బల్బు}}, {{t+check|te|దీపము}}, {{t+check|te|బుడ్డి}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To take the shape of a bulb; to [[swell]].\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=bblu|blub}}\n\n{{topics|en|Horticulture|Plant anatomy}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ca|la|bulbus}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n* {{audio|ca|LL-Q7026 (cat)-Marvives-bulb.wav|a=Barcelona}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{ca-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|ca|botany}} {{l|en|bulb}} {{gloss|bulb-shaped root of a plant}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|ca|bulb galàctic}}\n* {{l|ca|bulb raquidi}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|ca|bulbil}}\n* {{l|ca|bulbós}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:ca:IEC2}}\n\n{{C|ca|Plant anatomy}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|ro|fr|bulbe}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{ro-noun|m|bulbi}}\n\n# {{l|en|bulb}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{ro-noun-m}}"}}